<p>With the iPhone 6s, Apple has introduced a new feature called "3D Touch". App developers are able to use this technology by using it inside their apps or provide so called <code>UIApplicationShortcutItems</code> on the home screen which appear when your 3D Touch the corresponding app icon. I've seen quite a few people out there who wanted to know how you would be able to localize those. Here's how.</p>